The Kenya School of Laws’ Professor Patrick Loch Otieno Lumumba delivers the 16th Nelson Mandela Memorial Lecture at the Walter Sisulu University in Mthatha.  International renowned human rights activist, Professor Lumumba is in South Africa at the invitation of the National Heritage Council and O.R. Tambo District Municipality to speak at the Nelson Mandela Memorial Lecture to celebrate the centenary of Mandela. Lumumba spoke about Madiba when he touched down at Mthatha Airport. “First of all I must say this is a great occasion, and I want to remind us that Nelson Mandela is an Icon and icons never die.” 